Midgaard's interest in the Saltglass Reach is as the final land segment of the eastward trade chain before goods reach Mafdet's maritime network.
Charter mile marker fragments in the western Reach bands bear Midgaard-era registry catalog references on their eastern faces, confirming Midgaard's survey apparatus extended into the Reach during the Ash-and-Iron Decades.
The "contaminated-goods taxonomy" in modern caravan law — referencing "Fan-origin materials" from the Cinderteeth requiring separate handling codes — was developed partly in response to Reach market disruptions during post-Ashfall runoff events.
Midgaard tracks Reach Warden authority claims as a political variable: the Reach Wardens assert inherited Keeper survey rights over the Swift Line cairn chain; Midgaard does not recognize that claim but has not challenged it militarily because doing so would destabilize the only checkpoint system approximating legitimate caravan law.

